Police in Anambra State on Wednesday, said they have arrested one Leonard Aghano over alleged robbery in Nkpor in Idemili North local government area of Anambra State. The police spokesperson, Haruna Mohammed, in a statement, said the suspect, 27 years of Ekwulu village Umuoji, has been on the Police wanted list over cases of armed robbery and other heinous crimes. He said the suspect was apprehended by Police detectives attached to Ogidi Division around 2:45pm, following intelligence report. He said, “A Super Honda cub 90 motor cycle with registration number JJT312 QY robbed from one Ndubuisi lbegbu ‘m’ of Ire village Umuoji on 7/12/2018 and an iPhone robbed from Barr Obiora Nweze ‘m’ on 23/3/2019 including two matchets and a big hammer were recovered from him as exhibits.” The PPRO assured that the case was being investigated while efforts were on to apprehend his accomplices. Similarly, one Emmanuel Okonkwo (24) of Otoucha in the state has been arrested with a cut to size double barrel gun and two life ammunitions. The police spokesperson, Mohammed said the suspect was nabbed by Police operatives attached to Federal highway patrol along Oba road after intercepting a commercial bus and conducting search on the occupants. He added that the suspect was assisting the Police with useful information that could lead to the arrest of his accomplices.